        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">  the traceback is noisy for regular users.\n\nOn the plus side, if they end up in bug reports it's often much easier for plugin devs to figure out what went wrong. The first line is often not enough.\n\nimho `error` and `assert` should keep being verbose by default as those are mostly for unexpected cases. For expected errors there's notify with level=ERROR.\n\n\n> It is (should be) only shown if they expand it...\n\nOr this +1",
